  <body>
    <section id="section_ins_mxv_llb">
      <title>Converting YAML to JSON in Oxygen</title>
      <p id="p_x1g_cgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> includes a useful and simple tool for converting
        YAML files to JSON. It even works on files that consist of multiple YAML documents, each
        separated by three dashes (---), in which case the conversion creates multiple JSON files
        with a number in the name. </p>
      <p id="p_y1g_cgk_54b">The <uicontrol>YAML to JSON</uicontrol> action for invoking the tool can
        be found in the <menucascade product="developer editor json">
          <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
          <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
          <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
        </menucascade> menu.</p>
      <p id="p_z1g_cgk_54b">To convert a YAML document to JSON, follow these steps:</p>
      <ol id="ol_o2q_dxv_llb">
        <li id="li_abg_cgk_54b" irina="irina">
          <p id="p_bbg_cgk_54b">Select the <uicontrol>YAML to JSON</uicontrol> action from the
              <menucascade product="developer editor json">
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade><menucascade product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">
              <uicontrol>XML Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>JSON Tools</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> menu.</p>
          <p id="p_cbg_cgk_54b">The <uicontrol>YAML to JSON</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed:</p>
          <p id="p_dbg_cgk_54b">
            <fig id="fig_p2q_dxv_llb">
              <title>YAML to JSON Dialog Box</title>
              <image href="../img/yaml-to-json.png" id="image_q2q_dxv_llb"/>
            </fig>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li id="li_ebg_cgk_54b" irina="irina"> Choose or enter the <uicontrol>YAML URL</uicontrol> for the document you want to
          convert.</li>
        <li id="li_fbg_cgk_54b" irina="irina"> Choose the path of the <uicontrol>Output file</uicontrol> that will contain the
          resulting JSON document. </li>
        <li id="li_gbg_cgk_54b" irina="irina">
          <b>[Optional]</b> Select the <uicontrol>Open in Editor</uicontrol> option to open the
          resulting JSON document in the main editing pane. </li>
        <li id="li_hbg_cgk_54b" irina="irina"> Click the <uicontrol>Convert</uicontrol> button. </li>
      </ol>
      <p id="p_ibg_cgk_54b"><b>Result:</b> The original YAML document is now converted to a JSON document.</p>
    </section>
